<h1>How to participate in debates?</h1>

Debates are enabled by default (<a href="/settings">disable</a>)<br>

Users can only post one reply in a row.<br>

Every user can delete their own replies, and profile owners can delete replies under their comments.<br>

Replies are always public.

<h1>How to restrict other users from replying?</h1>

Profile owners can ban users from replying to their comments. Click the ðŸ”¨ icon next to a reply to ban a user, or visit the <a href="/ban">moderation page</a> to view and manage your bans.<br><br>

Profile owners can disable replying for other users by going to <a href="/settings">settings</a> and unchecking "Allow replies from all".  After that, profile owners can still enable debates selectively by including the words 'debate me' in some of their belief card comments.<br>

